SIMPLE: immodest
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Immodest
<hw>Im*mod"est</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>immodeste</ets>, L. <ets>immodestus</ets> immoderate; pref.
<ets>im-</ets> not + <ets>modestus</ets> modest. See
<er>Modest</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not limited to due bounds;
immoderate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Not modest; wanting in the reserve or restraint
which decorum and decency require; indecent; indelicate; obscene; lewd;
<as>as, <ex>immodest</ex> persons, behavior, words, pictures,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Immodest</qex> deeds you hinder to be wrought,⟦br⟧
But we proscribe the least <qex>immodest</qex> thought.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Indecorous; indelicate; shameless; shameful;
impudent; indecent; impure; unchaste; lewd; obscene.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Immodestly</ent>⟦br⟧
